description:
Secrets can’t stay hidden forever! So you think you know everything about what made Bruce Wayne into the Batman? Think again! In this jam-packed origins issue, we take you back ‘Before the New 52’, to show you how the building blocks of Batman and Robin like never before – and the revelations all play into some astounding new storylines across 2013! Don’t miss a second of the newest, greatest era of Batman ever!

Inside the latest issue:

THE DARK KNIGHT - CHILL IN THE AIR

Bruce Wayne’s parents have just been shot. But that’s not the end of the story – it’s just the beginning! Bruce believes his parents were killed because they made powerful enemies, and he’ll do anything to track down the truth

First printed in The Dark Knight #40

THE DARK KNIGHT - BRIGHT NEW YESTERDAY

It’s a new dawn in Gotham – for crime! Witness the birth of the Batman project… and see what make the original Red Hood tick. You’ll be seeing him again this year – he’s always good for a laugh…

First printed in The Dark Knight #40

BATMAN AND ROBIN - SOMEDAY NEVER COMES

The definitive origin story of the all-new Robin, Damian Wayne! From birth to his first meeting with this father, this one’s got it all. Plus – get to know the ruthless Talia al Ghul: 2013 is going to be her year!

First printed in Robin #0

description:
Welcome to the very first issue of Batman: The Dark Knight!

If you want to read about the darker side of Batman, Batman: The Dark Knight is the comic for you! Two deadly tales of Gotham in every issue, dripping with atmosphere, action, terror and mystery! See the artwork of David Finch and Tony Daniel on deluxe, oversized pages, while the Dark Knight's most infamous villains - and a cast of all-new creations - cause Gotham to shudder in horror!

Inside the first awesome issue:

Batman: The Dark Knight - 'Knight Terrors'

Three hundred inmates in Arkham Asylum have broken free from their 'unbreakable' restraints. It's up to Batman to contain the madness! Is it infectious? Did he really just see a white rabbit!?!

Batman: Detective Comics - Part One

Journalist Charlotte Rivers is in town to cover a spate of grisly murders and she has Bruce's heart all a-flutter! Meanwhile, Batman and Commissioner Gordon work together to uncover the terrible secrets of the Dollmaker.

If you want to read about the darker side of Batman, Batman: The Dark Knight is the comic for you! Two deadly tales of Gotham in every issue, dripping with atmosphere, action, terror and mystery! This month the madness continues in 'A Rush of Blood' as Batman begins to face his fears, while 'Playtime's Over' sees Bruce Wayne closing in on the horrendous Dollmaker and his fleshy creations!

Inside the latest issue:

Batman: The Dark Knight - 'A Rush of Blood'

After containing the madness of a break-out at Arkham Asylum, Bruce finds himself facing a mad and mutated Two-Face! What's going on? Is Bane involved? And who was that White Rabbit?

Batman: Detective Comics - 'Playtime's Over'

The secrets of The Dollmaker revealed, as Batman and Commissioner Gordon are dragged deeper into his web! Plus, does Charlotte Rivers have dangerous dirt on Batman?

If you want to read about the darker side of Batman, Batman: The Dark Knight is the comic for you! Two deadly tales of Gotham in every issue, dripping with atmosphere, action, terror and mystery! This month the madness continues in ‘Catch Me If You Can’ where the White Rabbit sets her sights on Batman, while 'Cold Blood’ sees Batman face another dark day!

Inside the latest issue:

Batman: The Dark Knight – ‘Catch Me If You Can’

The White Rabbit has Batman in her sights, but the Dark Knight is too busy dealing with a Venom-enhanced Joker! But is that all there is to the story? The mystery deepens!

Batman: Detective Comics – ‘Cold Blood’

There’s a patchwork man who looks like Jim Gordon at his feet, and that’s just the start of Batman’s latest dark day! What is the secret of the Dollmaker, and how does it relate to a young girl he has abducted?

When Gotham's citizens cry out in terror, one man stands between them and the chaos of the most vibrant - but deadly - city in the world. But what happens when even Batman is pushed to the edge and forced to confront his greatest fears? Find out inside!

Inside the latest issue:

Batman: The Dark Knight – ‘Welcome to the Jungle’

The rollercoaster continues with Poison Ivy missing, a contract on Batman's head, and guest-stars by the dozen! But who's behind the madness - and what is the secret of the White Rabbit?

Batman: Detective Comics – ‘The Main Event’

If Batman can survive against an insane volley of human dolls dressed like the Joker... what other surreal and bone-chilling terrors await him at the Dollmaker's hand?

Batman IS Gotham, to many minds, but when his own city turns against him, what then for Bruce Wayne? This issue, we see the Dark Knight confront the Scarecrow, the master of fear, and find himself lacking. Then, even faceless and missing, the Joker causes chaos... but that's nothing to what's in store from the Penguin!

Inside the latest issue:

BATMAN: THE DARK KNIGHT - HANDFUL OF DUST

Ambushed by the Scarecrow's fear gas, Batman is once again forced to confront his greatest terrors and the worst recesses of his mind - and to fight his greatest ally, the Man of Steel.

First printed in Batman: The Dark Knight #5

BATMAN: DETECTIVE COMICS - WHEEL OF MISFORTUNE

Batman faces off against citizens of Gotham City who think HE was responsible for skinning the Joker's face! And what's happening at the Penguin's casino - Iceberg Lounge?

First printed in Batman: Detective Comics #5

Things just keep getting more complicated for Bruce Wayne, especially when it comes to the women in his life. What tortures does the White Rabbit have in store for him, and what trap has she led Batman into this time? PLUS! With reporter Charlotte Rivers' life in the balance, Batman must discover what's really going down in the Penguin's floating casino!

Inside the latest issue:

BATMAN: THE DARK KNIGHT - RUN RABBIT RUN

With the Scarecrow's fear toxin pumping through his veins, Batman's search for Poison Ivy - and the truth about the mysterious White Rabbit - has been derailed. But vengeance - and the truth - is coming!

First printed in Batman: The Dark Knight #6

BATMAN: DETECTIVE COMICS - KILL GAME

Batman dives deep into the chill and deadly waters of the Penguin's casino - the Iceberg Lounge - to uncover Oswald Cobblepot's latest plot... and to rescue intrepid TV anchorwoman Charlotte Rivers!

First printed in Batman: Detective Comics #6

Welcome back to the Dark Knight, where two incredible stories come to their sense-shattering conclusions! Can Batman survive against Bane? Can he prevail against the Penguin?

Inside the latest issue:

BATMAN: THE DARK KNIGHT - THE FINAL CURTAIN

This is it! A super-smart, Toxin-enabled Bane is hunting Batman across Gotham City’s Harmon Island. Can Batman stay out of his reach long enough to crack the case?

BATMAN: DETECTIVE COMICS - THE SNAKE AND THE HAWK

Investigative reporter – and Bruce Wayne’s girlfriend – Charlotte Rivers has been stabbed. Can Batman save her?

Inside this issue:

Justice League - Part 6

The fate of the universe rests in the hands of Earth's newest team of super heroes! Superman has been captured by the demons from Apokolips and it's up to the World's Greatest Detective to get him back. Meanwhile, after failing to make a scratch on the all-powerful Darkseid, the rest of the Justice League restrategise and gear themselves up for another attack. Will their combined strength be enough to take out Darkseid and save the universe?

Action Comics: Superman Meets... The Collector Of Worlds Part 6

Superman vs Brainiac! The psychotic alien has captured the Man of Steel's adopted city, Metropolis, in a bid to add it to his 'collection' - a selection of alien artefacts from the across the universe. Among them is Kandor, the capital city of Superman's former homeworld, Krypton! Now Superman must fight Brainiac and his cyborg sentry, Metal-zero, to free Metropolis from Brainiac's grip! But issued with an ultimatum, Superman must choose whether to save Krypton or Metropolis! Will it be nature, or nurture?

Plus!

Aquaman: behind the scenes & a cool poster!
name: Justice League Part Six

description:
Inside this issue:

Justice League - Part 5

Darkseid, the greatest threat to the universe, has finally revealed himself to the Justice League! With the team now complete, can the world's most powerful group of misfits put aside their differences to save the Earth?

Action Comics: Superman's Doomsday Decision - Part 5

After fighting Metal-zero and the deadly Terminauts for the fate of Metropolis, the Man of Steel faces an even greater challenge when his beloved city is captured! Alone and outmatched against Metal-zero and his boss on board the ship which holds his city captive, Superman must push the limits of his powers like never before! Plus, secrets from the past are uncovered!

Green Lantern: Sinestro Part 5

After failing to free Sinestro's former homeworld from the tyranny of the Yellow Lantern's, a depowered Hal Jordan sits alone in his prison cell. Meanwhile, his 'partner', Sinestro, is forced to face up his past when confronted by the very people he tried to protect - and they're all wearing Green Lantern power rings!
name: Justice League Part Five

description: Shimmer City expected the earthquakes that shook the metropolis to its very foundation, but there was no way they were prepared for a prison break and they definitely weren't ready for this prison break! Voltes Shocklee and GoGo Diablo, an electrically enhanced human and an alien speed demon, are wreaking havoc on this desert oasis and only Jason and his new giant robot Chiron can put them back behind bars where they belong! It's more mechanized madness by J. Torres (Sidekicks, Copybook Tales) and Mike Norton (The Waiting Place, G.I. Joe)!
